I can see `appendTo = () => document.body` — the Popper renders the dropdown menu to `document.body` by default via a portal. This is critical. In tests, when the Select dropdown opens, its content (SelectList, SelectOption) is rendered into a portal appended to `document.body`.

Now, `screen.getByRole()` from testing-library searches the entire `document.body`, so elements in portals should still be found. Let me verify this is actually the case by checking if the test might have issues with timing/async rendering in the portal:

Looking at the test on line 119:
```tsx
const typeaheadDropdown = getTypeaheadDropdown(screen);
await user.click(typeaheadDropdown);

const option = screen.getByRole('option', {
  name: /^12 tib/i,
});
```

The `await user.click()` should wait for the click event to process. Then `screen.getByRole('option')` should find the option in the portal. Since `screen` searches `document.body` and the portal appends to `document.body`, this should work.

But wait — there might be a timing issue. The Popper uses `isVisible` to control rendering and may have animation delays. In tests with `userEvent.setup()`, the click is processed synchronously after the await. But if the portal content isn't rendered synchronously... Actually, React state updates from click handlers should be batched and flushed by the time `await user.click()` resolves.

Let me also look at the actual PF version installed in this project to verify Select behavior:

